urls.description: On December 2, 2019, an “untouchability” wall in Mettupalayam came down following heavy rainfall, killing 17 residents of Nadur village in Coimbatore district. Close to a year later, the upper caste man who had originally constructed the wall, allegedly to seperate himself from his Dalit neighbours, is re-constructing the wall, this time after securing permission from the local body. S Sivasubramaniam, a textile shop owner, had built a 20-feet-tall stone wall reportedly to fence his property and to isolate the Dalit settlement from his two-acre property.
urls.title: Mettupalayam 'caste' wall up again, less than a year after it claimed 17 lives
